summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming previous resolutions on Angola, 
Reaffirming commitment to preserve Angola's sovereignty and territorial integrity,
Welcoming steps by the Government of Angola and UNITA towards peace implementation,
Welcoming the reconvening of the Joint Commission and UN Mission in Angola,
Concerned about humanitarian effects on civilians,

1. Will consider the monitoring mechanism's additional report; 
2. Extends the mechanism's mandate for two months until 19 December 2002;
3. Requests an action plan from the mechanism including: 
- Consultations in Angola with Government and UNITA,
- Assessing possible UNITA measure violations,
- Locating frozen UNITA funds,
- Recommendations on frozen funds,
- Monitoring arms embargo and diamond trade;
4. Requests a further report by 13 December 2002 on violations and frozen funds;
5. Asks the Secretary-General to appoint experts to the mechanism;
6. Requests the Committee Chairman to submit the report by 19 December 2002;
7. Calls for States to cooperate with the mechanism;
8. Decides to cease certain measures against UNITA from 14 November 2002.
Decides to review, with a view to possible lifting of, measures in resolutions 864 (1993), 1127 (1997) and 1173 (1998) by 19 November 2002, considering all available information on implementation of peace accords; Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
